(384, 1, '2015-07-13 13:16:21', '2015-07-13 13:16:21', 'Athletes, adolescents and animals alike are ramping up their training as the seventh annual Cypress Triathlon in the <a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/">Bridgeland</a>® community nears. Starting on Saturday, July 25, the master planned community, which is owned by <a href="http://www.howardhughes.com/">The Howard Hughes Corporation</a>®, will kick off the weekend-long events with a Doggie Splash ‘N Dash and Youth Triathlon, followed by the Sprint Triathlon on Sunday, July 26.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n<div class="media media-element-container media-default">\r\n\r\n<img class="media-element file-default alignright" src="http://www.bridgeland.com/sites/default/files/BridgelandTriathlon.jpg" alt="" width="332" height="221" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nThe weekend’s first event, the Doggie Splash ‘N Dash, will pair up Fido and friend in a competition against other canine-loving teams for a 200-meter swim and one-mile run. In the Cypress Youth Triathlon that follows, children as young as six can choose to participate in a 100-meter pool swim, two-mile bike ride and three-quarters of a mile run. Depending on age and ability level, participants can also choose to modify the course. On Sunday, the Sprint Triathlon will include a 550-meter swim, 13-mile bike ride and 3.1-mile run. Compared to full triathlons, the Sprint Triathlon is a shorter distance race, making it popular among both new competitors and experienced athletes.\r\n\r\n“Out of all the triathlons we do, Bridgeland provides some of the best scenery,” said Aaron Palaian, Owner of Onurmark Productions and Director of the Cypress Triathlon. “Bridgeland provides a very welcoming and encouraging atmosphere for the competitors with residents out cheering racers along. They really make everyone feel at home.”\r\n\r\nThe race has come to be well-respected by triathletes across the Houston area, with the event selling out every year. In addition to the triathlon, Bridgeland hosts a number of competitive sporting events throughout the year.\r\n\r\n“It’s an honor to have the Cypress Triathlon within Bridgeland each year,” said Lona Shipp, Marketing Director for Bridgeland. “Our neighborhood is filled with running trails, biking paths and large lakes, making it an ideal location for a triathlon.”\r\n\r\nTo register or to volunteer to help throughout the weekend, visit <a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/">www.bridgeland.com</a>.', 'The Cypress Triathlon Planned for Weekend of July 25th in Bridgeland', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-cypress-triathlon-planned-for-weekend-of-july-25th-in-bridgeland', '', '', '2015-09-24 13:17:24', '2015-09-24 13:17:24', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/Bridgeland/?p=384', 0, 'post', '', 0);
