s made-up of brick, stucco or wood. Set behind the homes, garages are accessed via private rear lanes. Streetlights are reminiscent of those in River Oaks and other historic neighborhoods. Despite the nostalgic architecture, homes will have the modern features today’s buyers expect, such as high ceilings, large closets, media rooms and state-of-the-art kitchens and bathrooms. Additionally, the townhomes in the TND are a part of a new ‘lock-and-leave program’ that includes all yard work and exterior maintenance, allowing for stress-free upkeep.\r\n\r\nMany of the homesites face the waterway or a neighborhood park, and schools, churches and the Lakeland Village Center — a market square with shopping, services and dining — will be within walking distance. Also nearby is the Lakeland Activity Center, with an aquatic complex, tennis courts, boating and a 6,000-square-foot community center.\r\n\r\nGathering spots in Lakeland Heights include Festival Park, with a covered pavilion and Central Park, which includes two acres of green space, an open play area and a formal garden. The three-acre Rabbit Run has active open space and is across the street from the Lakeland Activity Center.\r\n\r\nTo receive information on available homesites in Lakeland Heights, visit <a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/">www.bridgeland.com</a> or call 281.304.5588. You can also view a video of Lakeland Heights <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=09fPfcjmB28">here</a>.', 'New Townhouse Product and Models in Lakeland Heights', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '388-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-24 13:18:11', '2015-09-24 13:18:11', '', 388, 'http://localhost:8888/Bridgeland/388-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(390, 1, '2015-06-30 13:30:47', '2015-06-30 13:30:47', 'During the month of July, buyers that purchase from participating home builders in Bridgeland® will be offered up to $5,000 in free electricity.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n<div class="media media-element-container media-default"><img class="media-element file-default alignright" src="http://www.bridgeland.com/sites/default/files/BridgelandPowertothePeople.jpg" alt="" width="389" height="259" /></div>\r\nThe perk is part of the master planned community’s popular ‘Power to the People’ promotion, which also includes a tour of available homes. Prospective buyers can enter a drawing to win a $1,000 Visa gift when registering at featured homes. Tour maps are available at Bridgeland’s Welcome Center or online at <a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/">www.bridgeland.com</a>. Homes will be open from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. Monday through Saturday, and 12 p.m. to 5 p.m. on Sundays.\r\n\r\n“Power to the People always sparks significant buyer interest,” said Peter Houghton, Vice President of Master Planned Communities for Bridgeland. “With nearly 50 available or under-construction homes, continuing low interest rates and valuable incentives such as this one, it’s a great time to buy in Bridgeland.”\r\n\r\nWith a range from traditional styles in Lakeland Heights® to semi-custom-built designs in Hidden Creek, buyers are sure to find a variety of homes in Bridgeland that fit their various tastes and specific needs. Hidden Creek will host 1,000 home sites, a 20-acre park, 142 acres of lakes and homes built by <a href="http://www.beazer.com/houston-TX/bridgeland-hidden-creek---55" target="_blank">Beazer Homes</a>,<a href="http://www.coventryhomes.com/houston/bridgelandhiddencreek">Coventry Homes</a>, <a href="http://www.darlinghomes.com/new-homes/texas/houston/cypress/bridgeland-hidden-creek-community" target="_blank">Darling Homes</a>, <a href="http://www.meritagehomes.com/search/houston-tx/bridgeland-hidden-creek/" target="_blank">Meritage Homes</a>, <a href="http://www.perryhomes.com/find-your-home/houston/bridgeland.aspx" target="_blank">Perry Homes</a>, <a href="http://www.ryland.com/find-your-new-home/11-houston/6311-bridgeland.html" target="_blank">Ryland Homes</a>, <a href="http://www.taylormorrison.com/new-homes/texas/houston/cypress/bridgeland-community" target="_blank">Taylor Morrison Homes</a>, <a href="http://www.lennar.com/New-Homes/Texas/Houston/Cypress/Bridgeland/Classic-and-Wentworth-Collections" target="_blank">Village Builders</a> and <a href="http://westin-homes.com/communities/details/6065" target="_blank">Westin Homes</a>. Homes in this area start at $300,000 and can exceed $1 million.\r\n\r\nLakeland Heights'' price range is from the $250s to $400s. Homes are built by <a href="http://www.davidweekleyhomes.com/new-homes/tx/houston/cypress/lakeland-heights-50" target="_blank">David Weekley Homes</a>, <a href="http://www.jkylehomes.com/lakeland-heights-bridgeland/" target="_blank">J. Kyle Homes</a> and <a href="http://www.perryhomes.com/Find-Your-Home/Houston/Bridgeland/Bridgeland---Townhomes-of-Lakeland-Heights" target="_blank">Perry Homes</a>. The community also provides walking-distance access to local schools, Lakeland Activity Center and the future Lakeland Village Center, where CVS/pharmacy® was recently announced as the anchor tenant.\r\n\r\nBridgeland won the 2013 “Master Planned Development of the Year” award from the Greater Houston Builders Association (GHBA), just one of the more than 100 accolades the community has received.', 'Bridgeland Offers up to $5,000 in Free Electricity to July Buyers', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'bridgeland-offers-up-to-5000-in-free-electricity-to-july-buyers', '', '', '2015-09-24 13:32:41', '2015-09-24 13:32:41', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/Bridgeland/?p=390', 0, 'post', '', 0),
