(408, 1, '2015-05-11 16:53:25', '2015-05-11 16:53:25', '15,000 attendees and 10,486 pounds of wild animals filled Oak Meadow Park at Bridgeland on Saturday, May 2<sup>nd</sup> for the eighth Nature Fest, an annual event that brings attention to the award-winning master planned community’s commitment to the environment and ecosystem. The star of the show, Jack Hanna, entertained three jam-packed audiences with a number of exotic companions, including a baby bear, an eagle, a kangaroo and a toucan.  Watch the video <a href="https://youtu.be/9Ipuw6Bnds4">here!</a>\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n<div class="media media-element-container media-default">\r\n\r\n<img class="media-element file-default" src="http://www.bridgeland.com/sites/default/files/Nature%20Fest%20One.jpg" alt="" width="2100" height="1249" />\r\n<div class="field field-name-field-modal-link field-type-link-field field-label-hidden field-wrapper"></div>\r\n</div>\r\nThousands of guests purchased tickets for pony rides, arts-and-crafts and an on-site petting zoo, helping raise more than $3,500 for a local charity that builds housing for families in need throughout Harris County. Since its inception, Nature Fest has enabled Bridgeland to donate nearly $35,000 to local non-profits.\r\n\r\n“We’re thrilled that this year’s Nature Fest was another success,” said Peter Houghton, Vice President of Master Planned Communities for Bridgeland. “Welcoming and offering the general public a day of fun in Bridgeland is something we truly enjoy doing, especially when we’re also able to raise money to put back into the community at the same time.”\r\n\r\nGuests enjoyed concessions from 20 local food trucks, roaming entertainers, educational reptile shows, unique goods from nature vendors and a kids’ zone that featured armadillo races, paddle boat rides, outdoor laser tag, an inflatable zone, a rock wall and a trackless train.\r\n\r\nNature lovers that sponsored the event included <a href="http://www.charlesdyeriv.com/"><u>Charles E. Dyer IV, DDS, MS, PC</u></a>, a returning Title Sponsor,<a href="http://avanti-sl.com/"><u>Avanti Senior Living Towne Lake</u></a>, <a href="http://www.beazer.com/"><u>Beazer Homes</u></a>, <a href="http://www.browngay.com/"><u>Brown &amp; Gay Engineers, Inc.,</u></a> <a href="http://www.costelloinc.com/"><u>Costello</u></a>, <a href="http://davidweekleyhomes.com/"><u>David Weekley Homes</u></a>, <a href="http://www.deltawestenv.com/"><u>Delta West Environmental</u></a>, <a href="https://www.directenergy.com/"><u>Direct Energy</u></a>, <a href="http://www.superdave.com/home.php"><u>Flory Team,</u></a> <a href="http://www.fcer.com/"><u>First Choice Emergency Room</u></a>, <a href="http://www.gulfcoastcorp.com/"><u>Gulf Coast Landscaping Services, Inc</u></a>., <a href="https://www.heb.com/"><u>H-E-B Fairfield</u></a>, <a href="http://landology.net/"><u>LANDology</u></a>, <a href="https://www.libertymutual.com/andreashotwell"><u>Liberty Mutual</u></a>, <a href="http://www.ljaengineering.com/"><u>LJA Engineers, Inc.,</u></a> <a href="http://mcguyerhomebuilders.com/"><u>MHI Homes</u></a>,<a href="http://www.perryhomes.com/"><u>Perry Homes</u></a>, <a href="http://waterworks.pepperconstruction.com/"><u>Pepper Lawson Waterworks</u></a>, <a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/houstonpettalk.com"><u>Pet Talk Magazine</u></a>, <a href="http://www.pcmi-us.com/"><u>Planned Community Management</u></a>, <a href="http://www.rkci.com/"><u>Raba Kistner</u></a>, <a href="http://www.republicservices.com/"><u>Republic Services</u></a>, <a href="http://www.rgmiller.com/"><u>R.G. Miller Engineers, Inc.</u></a>, <a href="http://www.sphllp.com/"><u>Schwartz, Page &amp; Harding L.L.P.</u></a>, <a href="http://www.severntrentservices.com/"><u>Severn Trent Services</u></a>, <a href="http://www.taylormorrison.com/new-homes/texas/houston/cypress/bridgeland-community"><u>Taylor Morrison Homes</u></a>, <a href="http://www.terrainsolutionsinc.com/"><u>Terrain Solutions, Inc</u></a>., <a href="http://www.texaspremierdental.com/"><u>Texas Premier Dental</u></a>, <a href="http://www.realestatewithamy.com/"><u>The Lippincott Team</u></a>, <a href="http://www.thelittlegym.com/houstoncopperfieldtx"><u>The Little Gym of Copperfield</u></a>, <a href="http://www.trueimageortho.com/"><u>True Image Orthodontics</u></a>, <a href="http://www.villagebuilders.com/index.aspx"><u>Village Builders</u></a>, <a href="http://www.westin-homes.com/"><u>Westin Homes</u></a>, Allgreen Associates, Grindel Consulting,  Municipal Accounts and Consulting and UT Physicians.\r\n\r\nNature Fest was titled “2014 Event of the Year” by the Greater Houston Builders Association. Bridgeland also hosts another large community event in October called Howl-O-Ween Fest.', 'Bridgeland''s Nature Fest Featuring Jack Hanna Attracts 15,000 People', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'bridgelands-nature-fest-featuring-jack-hanna-attracts-15000-people', '', '', '2015-09-24 16:58:18', '2015-09-24 16:58:18', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/Bridgeland/?p=408', 0, 'post', '', 0),
