</a>, a returning Title Sponsor,<a href="http://avanti-sl.com/"><u>Avanti Senior Living Towne Lake</u></a>, <a href="http://www.beazer.com/"><u>Beazer Homes</u></a>, <a href="http://www.browngay.com/"><u>Brown &amp; Gay Engineers, Inc.,</u></a> <a href="http://www.costelloinc.com/"><u>Costello</u></a>, <a href="http://davidweekleyhomes.com/"><u>David Weekley Homes</u></a>, <a href="http://www.deltawestenv.com/"><u>Delta West Environmental</u></a>, <a href="https://www.directenergy.com/"><u>Direct Energy</u></a>, <a href="http://www.superdave.com/home.php"><u>Flory Team,</u></a> <a href="http://www.fcer.com/"><u>First Choice Emergency Room</u></a>, <a href="http://www.gulfcoastcorp.com/"><u>Gulf Coast Landscaping Services, Inc</u></a>., <a href="https://www.heb.com/"><u>H-E-B Fairfield</u></a>, <a href="http://landology.net/"><u>LANDology</u></a>, <a href="https://www.libertymutual.com/andreashotwell"><u>Liberty Mutual</u></a>, <a href="http://www.ljaengineering.com/"><u>LJA Engineers, Inc.,</u></a> <a href="http://mcguyerhomebuilders.com/"><u>MHI Homes</u></a>,<a href="http://www.perryhomes.com/"><u>Perry Homes</u></a>, <a href="http://waterworks.pepperconstruction.com/"><u>Pepper Lawson Waterworks</u></a>, <a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/houstonpettalk.com"><u>Pet Talk Magazine</u></a>, <a href="http://www.pcmi-us.com/"><u>Planned Community Management</u></a>, <a href="http://www.rkci.com/"><u>Raba Kistner</u></a>, <a href="http://www.republicservices.com/"><u>Republic Services</u></a>, <a href="http://www.rgmiller.com/"><u>R.G. Miller Engineers, Inc.</u></a>, <a href="http://www.sphllp.com/"><u>Schwartz, Page &amp; Harding L.L.P.</u></a>, <a href="http://www.severntrentservices.com/"><u>Severn Trent Services</u></a>, <a href="http://www.taylormorrison.com/new-homes/texas/houston/cypress/bridgeland-community"><u>Taylor Morrison Homes</u></a>, <a href="http://www.terrainsolutionsinc.com/"><u>Terrain Solutions, Inc</u></a>., <a href="http://www.texaspremierdental.com/"><u>Texas Premier Dental</u></a>, <a href="http://www.realestatewithamy.com/"><u>The Lippincott Team</u></a>, <a href="http://www.thelittlegym.com/houstoncopperfieldtx"><u>The Little Gym of Copperfield</u></a>, <a href="http://www.trueimageortho.com/"><u>True Image Orthodontics</u></a>, <a href="http://www.villagebuilders.com/index.aspx"><u>Village Builders</u></a>, <a href="http://www.westin-homes.com/"><u>Westin Homes</u></a>, Allgreen Associates, Grindel Consulting,  Municipal Accounts and Consulting and UT Physicians.\r\n\r\nNature Fest was titled “2014 Event of the Year” by the Greater Houston Builders Association. Bridgeland also hosts another large community event in October called Howl-O-Ween Fest.', 'Bridgeland''s Nature Fest Featuring Jack Hanna Attracts 15,000 People', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '408-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-24 16:53:44', '2015-09-24 16:53:44', '', 408, 'http://localhost:8888/Bridgeland/408-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(410, 1, '2015-04-30 16:54:35', '2015-04-30 16:54:35', 'We hope you’re getting excited about Nature Fest this Saturday! The Bridgeland Development Team has worked diligently over the last seven months to plan an event that the entire family can enjoy. Here are some day-of logistics:\r\n<p align="center"><strong>8<sup>th</sup> Annual Nature Fest</strong></p>\r\n<p align="center"><strong>Saturday, May 2<sup>nd</sup></strong></p>\r\n<p align="center"><strong>Oak Meadow Park</strong></p>\r\n<p align="center"><strong>10 a.m. – 5 p.m.</strong></p>\r\n<p align="center"><!--more--></p>\r\n<strong><em>Parking:</em></strong> There will be a total of 12 shuttle stops this year - 11 in the neighborhood and one in the green space that’s between Warner Elementary School and Smith Middle School. The link to the map that follows (also below) only shows stops within Bridgeland, please follow directional signage on Fry to get to the 12th stop between Warner and Smith.<span class="file"><img class="file-icon" title="application/pdf" src="http://www.bridgeland.com/modules/file/icons/application-pdf.png" alt="" /><a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/sites/default/files/Shuttle%20Map.pdf" type="application/pdf; length=3626556">Download Download Download Download Download Shuttle Map.pdf</a></span>\r\n<div class="media media-element-container media-default">\r\n\r\n<img class="media-element file-default" src="http://www.bridgeland.com/sites/default/files/Shuttle%20Map.jpg" alt="" width="1539" height="1189" />\r\n<div class="field field-name-field-modal-link field-type-link-field field-label-hidden field-wrapper"></div>\r\n</div>\r\nFor the first time since we’ve hosted Nature Fest, we will not be utilizing Cy-Ranch’s parking lot because of school-related activities taking place on Saturday. Consequently, we’ve reserved space at Warner Elementary, Smith Middle School and in the open field in front of Lake Bridgeland.\r\n\r\nWith that being said, we kindly request that residents consider the following options before parking at any of the previously-mentioned locations:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Walk to your nearest shuttle stop and have a bus take you to Oak Meadow Park</li>\r\n	<li>Walk or bike to Oak Meadow Park – bike racks will be available at Oak Meadow Park</li>\r\n	<li>If space is available, park at Pope Elementary and take a shuttle to Oak Meadow Park</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFor those who need it, handicap parking is located at the front entrance of Oak Meadow Park.\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Attire:</em></strong> Please consider wearing closed-toed shoes or tennis shoes to the event, as stickers can be found throughout Oak Meadow Park’s grass. We also encourage bug spray and sunscreen!\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Activity Tickets:</em></strong> While admission to Nature Fest is free, pony rides, arts-and-crafts activity, face painting and petting zoo <strong>require tickets</strong>. Tickets are $1 each and can be purchased throughout the park on the day of the event*. <strong>The</strong> <strong>petting zoo and pony rides require three tickets each. The arts-and-crafts activity and face painting will require two tickets each</strong>. A portion of the funds raised will benefit Habitat for Humanity Northwest Harris County\r\n\r\n<em>* Cash only. There will be two ATMs on-site at Nature Fest.   </em>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Other Activities:</em></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Jack Hanna performances at 12 p.m., 1:30 p.m. and 3 p.m.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Autograph sessions following 12 p.m. and 1:30 p.m. performances</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Sky Kings Falconry shows at 11:30 a.m., 2:30 p.m. and 4 p.m.</li>\r\n	<li>Crocodile Encounter shows at 12:30 p.m. and 3:30 p.m.</li>\r\n	<li>Smith Middle School Band performance at 10:30 a.m.</li>\r\n	<li>Texas Stars Youth Choir performance at 11 a.m.</li>\r\n	<li>Exotic Petting Zoo</li>\r\n	<li>Armadillo Races</li>\r\n	<li>Face Painting</li>\r\n	<li>Kids’ Inflatable Zone</li>\r\n	<li>Rock Wall</li>\r\n	<li>Pony Rides</li>\r\n	<li>Fly Fishing Demonstration</li>\r\n	<li>Trackless Train</li>\r\n	<li>Arts-and-crafts Tent</li>\r\n	<li>Paddle Boat Rides</li>\r\n	<li>Smilebooth Photo Op</li>\r\n	<li>Farmers Market</li>\r\n	<li>Outdoor Laser Tag</li>\r\n	<li>Roaming Street Performers</li>\r\n	<li>Nature Exhibitors</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><em>Food Trucks</em></strong>: 19 <a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/events/nature-fest">food trucks</a> will be on-site at Nature Fest\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Pictures:</em></strong> We love interacting with event attendees on social media! At the event, be sure to tag <strong>#NatureFest15</strong>and<strong> #BridgelandBalance</strong> in your pictures. We’re looking forward to seeing Nature Fest through your eyes.\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Residents </strong></em><em><strong>Entering/Exiting Bridgeland: </strong></em>Excluding homeowners in First Bend, residents should be able to enter and exit the community through Hidden Pass and can consequently avoid congestion on North Bridgeland Lake Parkway.\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions or concerns, feel free to call the Welcome Center at 281.304.5588. You can also easily reach us via <a href="https://www.facebook.com/Bridgelandcommunity?ref=hl">Facebook</a>.\r\n\r\nHope you all have a wild time on Saturday!', 'Nature Fest Parking and Logistics', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'nature-fest-parking-and-logistics', '', '', '2015-09-24 16:58:40', '2015-09-24 16:58:40', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/Bridgeland/?p=410', 0, 'post', '', 0),
