(431, 1, '2015-02-12 17:12:57', '2015-02-12 17:12:57', 'Registration is now open for Bridgeland’s BBQ Cook-off, an annual event that’s back for its sixth year on Saturday, March 28 from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. at Oak Meadow Park, 17730 House Hahl Road.<span class="caption right media-image alignright size-medium wp-image-2488 media-element file-teaser"><a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/files/bridgelandbbq-1-300x200jpg"><img src="http://www.bridgeland.com/sites/default/files/styles/medium/public/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/BridgelandBBQ-1-300x200.jpg?itok=5j8w8bVH" alt="BridgelandBBQ 1" width="220" height="147" /></a></span>\r\n\r\nFor an entry fee of $40, local pit masters can battle for bragging rights and first-place prizes in categories like ‘Best Ribs’ and ‘People’s Choice.’ On top of cooking and sampling BBQ, attendees can also take part in a jalapeno eating contest, enjoy an on-site dunking booth and peruse through a showcase of new and classic cars, trucks and motorcycles.\r\n\r\nFor more information or to register, visit <a href="http://www.bridgelandlife.com/">www.bridgelandlife.com</a> or call 281-304-1318.', 'Bridgeland Recognized as the Cy-Fair Area''s Medium-sized Business of the Year', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'bridgeland-recognized-as-the-cy-fair-areas-medium-sized-business-of-the-year', '', '', '2015-09-24 17:47:23', '2015-09-24 17:47:23', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/Bridgeland/?p=431', 0, 'post', '', 0),
