(438, 1, '2015-01-09 18:13:28', '2015-01-09 18:13:28', 'Bridgeland''s first market of the year on Sunday, Jan. 11 from 12:30-3:30 p.m. will include the following:\r\n\r\n<span class="caption none media-image alignright size-medium wp-image-2371"><a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/files/bridgeland-august-farmers-market-198x30010jpg"><img src="http://www.bridgeland.com/sites/default/files/styles/medium/public/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/Bridgeland-August-Farmers-Market-198x300_10.jpg?itok=ykbopv5J" alt="Bridgeland August Farmers Market" width="145" height="220" /></a></span>\r\n\r\nFree class on juicing by YLive Juice at 1:00 p.m.:\r\nPam Ennis, a natural foods chef and owner of YLive Juice, combines her passion for whole foods, healing and healthy living in this great class. You will have the opportunity to learn her unique approach to health and wellness through juicing. Special emphasis on:\r\n• The benefits of juicing, juicing vs. blending, types of juicers, how to select a juicer\r\n• How to do your own at-home juice cleanse\r\n• Learning what to juice\r\n• Juicing for weight loss\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nProduce in Season:\r\nTomatoes, snow peas, cucumbers, radishes, peppers, lettuce, spinach, kale, collards, cabbage, butternut, spaghetti and yellow squash, sweet potatoes, red potatoes, onions and strawberries.\r\n\r\nSpecial Community Highlight:\r\nBridgeland''s own "2015 Calendars" will be proudly presented by The Bridgeland Photography Group. These beautiful, full-size color photo calendars depict Bridgeland activities, landscapes, animal life and plant life. All photographs were taken by residents that participate in The Bridgeland Photography Group. Limited quantities available.', 'The Farmers Market at Bridgeland Hosts First Market of 2015', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-farmers-market-at-bridgeland-hosts-first-market-of-2015', '', '', '2015-09-24 18:13:59', '2015-09-24 18:13:59', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/Bridgeland/?p=438', 0, 'post', '', 0);
