(440, 1, '2015-01-09 18:15:19', '2015-01-09 18:15:19', 'Darling Homes is taking lot reservations and selling houses in the new Hidden Creek neighborhood of Bridgeland, where it plans to debut models homes early this year.\r\n\r\n“Our homes at Bridgeland will include the designs and special touches that today’s buyer demands and Houston homebuyers have come to expect from us,” Amy Rino, president of Darling Homes’ Houston division, said in an announcement. “Home buyers will find thoughtfully designed floor plans paired with a variety of options that will include media rooms, sun rooms, expansive master suites and more.”\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nAfter a stall in home building, construction is under way in the 11,400-acre master planned community at Fry Road near U.S. 290 northwest of Houston.\r\n\r\nThe Howard Hughes Corp., developer of Bridgeland and The Woodlands, got the green light from the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers to proceed with the Hidden Creek neighborhood last year.\r\n\r\nAmenities in Hidden Creek include the 20-acre Lakeland Village Park, with a heated lap pool, a fenced dog park, tennis courts, playgrounds, walking trails, skate park and basketball court. Residents will be able to enjoy activities such as canoeing and kayaking at Josey Lake, which will be more than three miles long.\r\n\r\nDarling Homes is a division of Taylor Morrison Home Corp. based in Scottsdale, Ariz.', 'Darling Homes Selling in Hidden Creek', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'darling-homes-selling-in-hidden-creek', '', '', '2015-09-24 18:16:44', '2015-09-24 18:16:44', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/Bridgeland/?p=440', 0, 'post', '', 0),
