(447, 1, '2014-11-10 18:55:34', '2014-11-10 18:55:34', 'Community members are encouraged to ‘gobble up’ their spots in Hannah’s Turkey Trot at Bridgeland, a second annual 5K and 10K scheduled for Saturday, Nov. 22 at 8 a.m. in the 11,400-acre master planned community.<span class="caption none media-image alignright size-medium wp-image-2449"><a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/files/bridgelandturkeytrot-300x2254jpg"><img class="alignright" src="http://www.bridgeland.com/sites/default/files/styles/medium/public/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/BridgelandTurkeyTrot-300x225_4.jpg?itok=loG8EQ1u" alt="BridgelandTurkeyTrot" width="220" height="165" /></a></span>\r\n\r\nUntil Nov. 21, participants can register for the 5K for $30 or the 10K for $40, with all proceeds benefiting the Juvenile Diabetes Research Foundation (JDRF), a global organization with scientific resources, regulatory influence and a plan in place to treat, prevent and eventually cure type 1 diabetes (T1D).\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nThe race’s namesake, 13-year-old Hannah Stewart, was diagnosed with T1D at the age of seven and urges people to partake in the race.\r\n“By donating today, you can help JDRF fund research that impacts the lives of the millions of children, adults and families challenged by T1D every single day,” said Stewart. “With your support, we will create a world without T1D and turn ‘Type One’ into ‘Type None’.”\r\n\r\nTru Tri Sports, the local store organizing the event, expects around 350 participants and will distribute awards to male and female competitors in various age groups.\r\n\r\nFor more information on Hannah’s Turkey Trot at Bridgeland or to register, visit <a href="http://www.hannahsturkeytrot.com/">www.hannahsturkeytrot.com</a>.', 'Bridgeland Hosts Second Annual Turkey Trot Nov. 22', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'bridgeland-hosts-second-annual-turkey-trot-nov-22', '', '', '2015-09-24 18:56:06', '2015-09-24 18:56:06', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/Bridgeland/?p=447', 0, 'post', '', 0),
