(451, 1, '2014-10-30 18:56:52', '2014-10-30 18:56:52', 'Between the star-studded stage performances, parades of pooches on the runway and an assortment of crowd-and-canine approved activities, nearly 7,000 people and pups had a ‘dog gone’ good time at Bridgeland’s annual Howl-O-Ween Fest on Saturday, Oct. 25th.<span class="caption none media-image alignright size-medium wp-image-2441"><a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/files/hfest3-300x2534jpg"><img class="alignright" src="http://www.bridgeland.com/sites/default/files/styles/medium/public/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/HFest3-300x253_4.jpg?itok=MFMFYg8t" alt="HFest3" width="220" height="186" /></a></span>\r\n\r\nAmidst the day’s fun, more than $3,500 was raised for local pet rescue groups, bringing the total amount collected during the last six Howl-O-Ween Fests to approximately $12,400.\r\n\r\n“We’re thrilled that this year’s Howl-O-Ween Fest was another success,” said Peter Houghton, Vice President of Master Planned Communities for Bridgeland. “Welcoming and offering the general public a day of fun in Bridgeland is something we truly enjoy doing, especially when we’re also able to raise money to put back into the community while doing it.”\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nThe former winners of America’s Got Talent, the Olate Dogs, dazzled audiences with two stage performances filled with rescue dogs doing back flips, riding scooters and jumping rope. David Chicken and his four-pound Chihuahua, Chacie, also presented their high-energy, Emmy-award winning lineup of songs to spectators. Other guests enjoyed concessions from 14 local food trucks, pumpkin decorating, unique goods from dozens of pet vendors and a fall fest area hosted by Bridgeland’s on-site church, The Foundry.\r\n\r\nAlthough entrance into the event and some activities were free, a few fetched a small fee to benefit participating animal rescue groups including Adore Houston, Buster''s Friends, Cocker Spaniel Rescue of East Texas, English Bulldog Rescue Group Network, German Shorthaired Pointer Rescue of North Texas, Great Dane Rescue of Southeast Texas, Husky Haven, Pughearts, Rescued Pets Movement Inc., Special Pals Shelter, The Boykin Spaniel Rescue and the Weimaraner Rescue of Texas\r\n\r\nDog-lovers that sponsored the event included Charles E Dyer IV, DDS, MS, PC, Beazer Homes, The Lippincott Team - Better Homes and Gardens, Schwartz, Page and Harding, LLP, The Flory Team, Brown and Gay Engineers, Inc., The J. Beard Real Estate Company, Village Builders, The Goddard School, LJA Engineering, Perry Homes, Realty Associates, David Weekley Homes, North Houston Veterinary Specialists, Delta West, RE/MAX Lakeland, Dawn Fore Team, TBG Partners, Inc., Westin Homes, Coldwell Banker United Realtors, Halff Associates, Inc., Severn Trent Services, Raba Kistner, Doody Calls, H-E-B Fairfield, Blackhorse Animal Hospital, Mix 96.5, First Choice Emergency Room and City Ambulance, Republic Services, Liberty Mutual Insurance, The Little Gym, Houston Landscapes, Ryland Homes and Zippy Shell Mobile Self Storage and Moving.\r\n\r\nVoted the 2013 “Master Planned Community of the Year” by the Greater Houston Builder Association, Bridgeland hosts two large community events a year, Howl-O-Ween Fest in October and Nature Fest in April. For more information on the community or its events, visit <a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/">www.bridgeland.com</a>, <a href="https://www.facebook.com/Bridgelandcommunityor">https://www.facebook.com/Bridgelandcommunityor</a><a href="https://twitter.com/BridgelandTweet">https://twitter.com/BridgelandTweet</a>.', 'Crowd of People and Pups Dig Bridgeland''s Sixth Howl-O-Ween Fest', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'crowd-of-people-and-pups-dig-bridgelands-sixth-howl-o-ween-fest', '', '', '2015-09-24 18:57:45', '2015-09-24 18:57:45', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/Bridgeland/?p=451', 0, 'post', '', 0),
