e stayed humble and didn’t let it get to his head.”\r\n\r\nIn 2012, the Olate Dogs’ unique performances landed them a spot on America’s Got Talent, where they went on to win the million-dollar prize and the opportunity to star in a show in Las Vegas, the first non-singing act to do so.\r\n\r\n“Being on America’s Got Talent was such a learning experience for us because we were performing alongside a bunch of amazing acts,” said Olate Jr. “Winning has opened up so many doors and opportunities for us.”\r\n\r\nThe Olate Dogs now travel around the country performing, with their next show at Bridgeland’s Howl-O-Ween Fest on Saturday, Oct. 25 from 10 am – 4 pm. The sixth annual event raises funds for Houston-area rescue groups, a cause near to the Olate Dogs'' hearts.\r\n\r\n“My dad likes to tell me that he doesn’t know if he rescued the animals or if they rescued him,” said Olate Jr. “Who knows where he’d be if he hadn’t found those dogs.”\r\n\r\nTo learn more about Howl-O-Ween Fest, visit <a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/howl-o-ween-fest.com">www.bridgeland.com/howl-o-ween-fest.com</a>. Bridgeland is a wholly-owned subsidiary of The Howard Hughes Corporation and part of The Woodlands Development Company.', 'Member of Olate Dogs Reflects on the Group''s Humble Start', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '466-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-24 19:06:59', '2015-09-24 19:06:59', '', 466, 'http://localhost:8888/Bridgeland/466-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(468, 1, '2015-09-24 19:07:37', '2015-09-24 19:07:37', 'Pooches and people alike are sure to have a ‘dog-gone’ good time at <a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/">Bridgeland’s</a> Howl-O-Ween Fest Saturday, October 25 as the Olate Dogs, a crew that won <i>America’s Got Talent</i> in 2012, wows local audiences with its crowd-and-canine approved performances from 10 am to 4 pm at Oak Meadow Park, 17730 House Hahl Road.<span class="caption none media-image alignright size-medium wp-image-2393"><a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/files/xg6lzogpwiiopxxd0-dccnbmhupqf68jan9a0qp91i-231x3004jpg"><img class="alignright" src="http://www.bridgeland.com/sites/default/files/styles/medium/public/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/xg6lZOgpwIIoPxXd_0-DCCNbmhUPqF68JAn9a0qP91I-231x300_4.jpg?itok=UGOiP9Ti" alt="Howl-O-Ween Fest to Feature Winner of America’s Got Talent on October 25th" width="169" height="220" /></a></span>\r\n\r\nAfter winning the seventh season of <i>America’s Got Talent </i>and walking away with the million-dollar prize, Richard and Nicholas Olate, along with 10 of their pets-turned-performers, continued to delight animal-loving audiences at their own show in Las Vegas, NBA halftime performances and various circuses around the country. Now the group is set to leave Howl-O-Ween Fest attendees howling for more with two performances at the event, one at 11:30 am and the other at 2 pm.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nAnother star-studded entertainer, David Chicken, will perform alongside his four-pound Chihuahua, Super Chacie. The duo will present their Emmy-awarded lineup of songs, which fuse high-energy music and motivational messages for an interactive experience the entire family will enjoy.\r\n\r\n“We’re very excited to host Howl-O-Ween Fest for a sixth year,” said Peter Houghton, Vice President of Master Planned Communities for Bridgeland. “Guests will really enjoy the entertainers and activities we’ll have on site and also catch a glimpse at what life is like in our community.”\r\n\r\nThe ‘haute-dog’ fashion show, a crowd favorite each year, is sure to amuse audience members of all ages as guests and their furry friends pair up for a heated costume contest. Splash Dogs’ dock-diving competition, Houston Canine Frisbee Disc Club’s high-flying performance and chalk artist Anat Ronen are also back by popular demand.\r\n\r\nSome of Houston’s favorite food trucks will be on-site to satisfy hunger growls, including Bernie’s Burger Bus, Coreanos, Happy Endings, Kona Ice, The Golden Grill, The Waffle Bus, Tila’s Taco Truck and Pho’jita Fusion. Also lined up are animal-oriented vendors, on-site dog adoptions, pumpkin decorating and trick-or-treating for kids and their pets. The Foundry, a church located in Bridgeland, will again host its Fall Fest area, where younger attendees can play at an inflatable park, compete on an obstacle course and test their riding skills on a mechanical bull.\r\n\r\nAlthough entrance into the event and some activities are free, a few will fetch a small fee to benefit participating animal rescue groups. While fun will be untamed at Howl-O-Ween Fest, all animals must remain on a leash, wear a current rabies tag and be up-to-date on all vaccinations.  To keep the event enjoyable for everyone, aggressive pooches will be asked to leave.\r\n\r\nFellow dog-lovers helping sponsor Howl-O-Ween Fest include <a href="http://charlesdyeriv.com/" target="_blank">Charles E Dyer IV, DDS, MS, PC</a>, <a href="http://www.beazer.com/houston-TX/bridgeland-hidden-creek---55" target="_blank">Beazer Homes</a>, <a href="http://realestatewithamy.com/" target="_blank">The Lippincott Team - Better Homes and Gardens</a>, <a href="http://www.sphllp.com/" target="_blank">Schwartz, Page and Harding, LLP</a>, <a href="http://floryteam.com/" target="_blank">The Flory Team</a>, <a href="http://www.browngay.com/" target="_blank">Brown and Gay Engineers, Inc.</a>,  <a href="http://www.villagebuilders.com/houston/community.aspx?c=4497" target="_blank">Village Builders</a>, <a href="http://www.goddardschool.com/houston/cypress-creek-lakes-tx" target="_blank">The Goddard School</a><a href="http://www.sphllp.com/" target="_blank">,</a> <a href="http://deltawestenv.com/" target="_blank">Delta West</a>, <a href="http://www.tbg-inc.com/" target="_blank">TBG Partners, Inc.</a>, <a href="http://westin-homes.com/communities/details/6065" target="_blank">Westin Homes</a><a href="http://www.tbg-inc.com/" target="_blank">,</a> <a href="http://halff.com/" target="_blank">Halff Associates, Inc.</a>, <a href="http://www.doodycalls.com/" target="_blank">Doody Calls</a>, <a href="http://www.fcer.com/" target="_blank">First Choice Emergency Room and City Ambulance</a> and <a href="http://www.republicservices.com/site/houston/en/pages/location.aspx" target="_blank">Republic Services</a>.\r\n\r\nMore details and event updates can be found at <a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/howl-o-ween-fest">www.bridgeland.com/howl-o-ween-fest</a>. Also, see pictures from last year’s event, which drew more than 7,000 dog lovers, on Bridgeland’s Facebook page,<a href="http://www.facebook.com/BridgelandCommunity">www.facebook.com/BridgelandCommunity</a>.', 'Howl-O-Ween Fest to Feature Winner of America''s Got Talent on October 25th', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'howl-o-ween-fest-to-feature-winner-of-americas-got-talent-on-october-25th', '', '', '2015-09-24 19:07:37', '2015-09-24 19:07:37', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/Bridgeland/?p=468', 0, 'post', '', 0),
