(490, 1, '2014-05-09 19:43:48', '2014-05-09 19:43:48', 'The Farmers Market at <a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/">Bridgeland</a> will salute mothers with free orchids 12:30-3:30 p.m. Mother’s Day, May 11.\r\n\r\nOrchid Obsession, a local grower, wholesaler and retailer of orchids, bromeliads and other tropical plants, will give a free “Scent of a Woman” orchid to every mother who visits its booth.<span class="caption none media-image alignright size-medium wp-image-2325"><a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/files/bridgelandorchidjpg-214x3009jpg"><img class="alignright" src="http://www.bridgeland.com/sites/default/files/styles/medium/public/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/BridgelandOrchid.jpg-214x300_9.jpg?itok=zQ4A5960" alt="BridgelandOrchid.jpg" width="157" height="220" /></a></span>\r\n\r\n“I started my practice of giving away orchids as a way of honoring the memory of my mother who passed away 12 years ago,” said Bruce Cameron, owner of Orchid Obsession. “There is no purchase required, just let me know that you are a mom.”\r\n\r\nClose to 30 additional vendors will have booths set up as well, selling everything from craft-brewed coffee, natural cat and dog treats, pastured meats, cage-free eggs, local honey and homemade bread.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nA variety of seasonal produce like sugar snap peas, radishes, squash, dew berries, cucumbers and okra will also be for sale.\r\n\r\nThe Farmers Market at Bridgeland is held the second Sunday of each month near Bridgeland’s Lakeland Activity Center, 16902 Bridgeland Landing. To see a full list of participating vendors, visit <a href="http://www.farmersmarketatbridgeland.org/">www.farmersmarketatbridgeland.org.</a>\r\n\r\nLearn more about Bridgeland, a wholly owned subsidiary of <a href="http://www.howardhughes.com/">The Howard Hughes Corporation</a> and part of <a href="http://www.thewoodlands.com/">The Woodlands Development Company</a>, at <a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/">www.bridgeland.com</a>.', 'The Farmers Market