(494, 1, '2014-04-21 20:02:14', '2014-04-21 20:02:14', 'Students and staff at Pope Elementary, a Cy-Fair ISD school, are preparing to read their way into history books, Friday, April 25, with an attempt to break the world record for the largest reading lesson.\r\n\r\nBecky Koop, principal of the one-year old school in Bridgeland, says they will need 289 students and teachers in attendance in order to break the record.\r\n\r\n“It’s going to be fun, but also educational. In fact, the lesson will be based upon a format used in our students’ language arts classes,” said Koop. “We’re going to team up older and younger children and have them interact and collaborate throughout the lesson.”\r\n\r\nKoop, who will lead the lesson alongside a few teachers, says they plan to have around 900 participants and will hold the attempt outside. In order to challenge the exiting record holder, the entire event must be recorded and each person will have to pass through a turnstile in order to calculate an exact attendance number.\r\n\r\n“The kids are so excited about the attempt,” said Koop. “Breaking it would be such a fantastic way to end our first year; it’s a wonderful legacy to leave behind.”\r\n\r\nPope Elementary, noted for its environmentally-sensitive and unique design, was built after Bridgeland donated the space for the school in early 2012. The development team at Bridgeland worked closely with Cy-Fair ISD and VLK Architects to ensure Pope took advantage of its park-like setting.  Consequently, a glass-front library, second-floor reading loft and a multipurpose observation deck were designed to overlook Cypress Lake in Bridgeland.\r\n\r\nThe development continues to support its pioneer school and most recently donated $5,000 for new playground equipment like a climbing dome, volleyball equipment and additional picnic tables.\r\n\r\nPope is the first of nine planned schools that will eventually be nestled within the community, including six elementaries, two middle schools and at least one high school. The development’s “cradle-to-career” philosophy also includes plans for daycares, private facilities and opportunities for higher education.\r\n\r\nLearn more about Bridgeland, a wholly owned subsidiary of <a href="http://www.howardhughes.com/">The Howard Hughes Corporation</a> and part of <a href="http://www.thewoodlands.com/">The Woodlands Development Company</a>, at <a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/">www.bridgeland.com</a>.', 'Pope Elementary Students and Staff Attempt to Break World Record', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'pope-elementary-students-and-staff-attempt-to-break-world-record', '', '', '2015-09-24 20:02:42', '2015-09-24 20:02:42', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/Bridgeland/?p=494', 0, 'post', '', 0),
