(496, 1, '2014-04-11 20:02:48', '2014-04-11 20:02:48', 'Although The Farmers Market at <a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/">Bridgeland</a> is held on a monthly basis, its gatherings are hardly monotonous. With a variety of new vendors and another free, hands-on gardening class, the market on Sunday, April 13, from 12:30 – 3:30 p.m. is sure to please both new and returning attendees.\r\n\r\nPhoebe Lake of New Leaf Nursery, a regular vendor at the market, will lead the 1 p.m. class. Lake, a retired Master Gardener and  Certified Nursery Professional, will teach how to grow seasonal varieties of basil, rosemary, thyme, oregano, lavender, mint and  other popular herbs.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nFour new merchants are joining this month, for a total of 36 market vendors.  The first, Esti’s Best, will sell its gluten, dairy and  soy-free desserts, which are also paleo-friendy. Shiner Pork, another first-time merchant, will offer its Heritage pork and grass-fed  beef.  Shoppers can also stop by Salinas Salsa Works’ tent, where the team will sell the green sauce that won them first place in the  2013 Houston Hot Sauce Festival. Lastly, Righteous Bros. Coffee will offer its handcrafted, specialty coffee.\r\n\r\nCat Reynolds, Abby Weeks and Jobie Burr, Cy-Ranch High School students, will provide on-site entertainment by performing a few  original songs in addition to acoustic covers.\r\n\r\nOpen to the public, The Farmers Market at Bridgeland is held on the second Sunday of each month near Bridgeland’s Lakeland  Activity Center, 16902 Bridgeland Landing. To see a full list of participating vendors, visitwww.farmersmarketatbridgeland.org.  Learn more about Bridgeland, a wholly owned subsidiary of <a href="http://www.howardhughes.com/">The Howard Hughes Corporation</a> and part of <a href="http://www.thewoodlands.com/">The Woodlands Development Company</a>, at <a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/">www.bridgeland.com</a>.', 'The Farmers Market at Bridgeland Spices it up April 13'