(502, 1, '2014-03-07 20:07:46', '2014-03-07 20:07:46', 'Plump, juicy tomatoes will be the highlight of The Farmers Market at <a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/">Bridgeland</a>, 12:30 – 3:30 p.m. Sunday, March 9, as a local gardener leads a class focused on harvesting home-grown varieties of the fruit.<span class="caption none media-image alignright size-medium wp-image-2275"><a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/files/bridgelandmarchmarket-225x3004jpg"><img class="alignright" src="http://www.bridgeland.com/sites/default/files/styles/medium/public/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/BridgelandMarchMarket-225x300_4.jpg?itok=q4IVPZZS" alt="BridgelandMarchMarket" width="165" height="220" /></a></span>\r\n\r\nStephanie Baker, who completed her Texas Master Gardener Certification in 2002 and owns <a href="http://www.readytogrowgardens.com/blog/about/">Ready to Grow Gardens</a>, a curriculum-oriented gardening program for elementary students, will be teaching the 1 p.m. class, which is free and open to the public. Baker says growing tomatoes is easy, but warned that some key factors determine if a plant is fruitful or not.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n“I’ll be teaching how to select the right plant, what type of soil to use, ideal planting locations and tips on fertilizing,” said Baker, who led a similar course last year. “The group that attended the class in 2013 had a lot of success after following my recommendations.”\r\n\r\nNew Leaf Nursery, a regular vendor at the monthly market, will offer more than 40 types of tomato plants, including heirlooms and hybrids. Additional specialty merchants will sell fresh produce, Texas honey, homemade pastas, grass-fed meats, floral-infused vinegars and other gourmet products.\r\n\r\nShoppers will wander the market to the tunes of <a href="http://griftersandshills.com/">Grifters &amp; Shills</a>, a high-energy folk band that’s returning for the second time after numerous requests from attendees.\r\n\r\nOpen to the public, The Farmers Market at Bridgeland is held on the second Sunday of each month near Bridgeland’s Lakeland Activity Center, 16902 Bridgeland Landing. To see a full list of participating vendors, visit<a href="file:///C:/Users/audrey.roeder/AppData/Local/Microsoft/Windows/Temporary%20Internet%20Files/Content.Outlook/0CHEWO1Q/www.farmersmarketatbridgeland.org">www.farmersmarketatbridgeland.org</a>.  Learn more about Bridgeland, a wholly owned subsidiary of <a href="http://www.howardhughes.com/">The Howard Hughes Corporation</a> and part of <a href="http://www.thewoodlands.com/">The Woodlands Development Company</a>, at <a href="http://www.bridgeland.com/">www.bridgeland.com</a>.', 'The Farmers Market at Bridgeland Springs to Life March 9', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-farmers-market-at-bridgeland-springs-to-life-march-9', '', '', '2015-09-24 20:08:59', '2015-09-24 20:08:59', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/Bridgeland/?p=502', 0, 'post', '', 0),
